name: candy apple espresso roast  instinct roastery  200 gram
description: 50 toraja washed  20 colombia sequoias watermelon  30 flores natural a little fun we have on the roastery when we stumble on this sample on our cupping table we thought what if we make a blend that tastes like candy and apple at the same time and just like that this blend is made out of a combination weve never thought before with our toraja pangopango washed as our base we give a combination with flores natural which enhances the sweetness and mouthfeel together with toraja and the colombia sequoias added that fun with notes that has two layers apple and also watermelon notes this blend will give you a sense of eating fruit candy a little gift from us to you merry christmas

name: ethiopia tima washed  instinct roastery  150 gram
description: region  guji process  washed variety  74110 altitude  2150 masl this ethiopia flaunts its light body and this tima we bring tima with sweeter notes that reminds you of peach guji has been constantly be the region that produces complex and high quality ethiopian coffee the condition of its terroir and also high altitude which revolves around 20002150 masl creating a slow process of ripe cherry which also resulting in complex and delicate flavor this is for you who looks for light bodied coffee with notes of peach and layer of bergamot with that classic floral notes of ethiopia

name: espresso roast kenya tatu  instinct roastery  200 gram
description: process  natural region  kiambu county farm  tatu estate variety  sl28  sl34 releasing espresso roast has been nothing but a joy for us offering you different kind of flavor spectrum for your daily espresso is our goals in through this platform this time we bring you natural kenyan coffee from tatu estate tatu estate is a part of kofinaf company a historical and big producer of coffee in kenya it has its own record of consistently bringing good coffee on your cupping table and furthermore this natural processed coffee less known in kenya where most of them are washed is bringing something unique yet excellent in its juiciness and sweetness this is a balanced cup of espresso in its fruitiness that reminds you of red fruits like currant and pomegranate yet sweetness that taste caramelish

name: ethiopia sidama baturo  instinct roastery  150 gram
description: process  anaerobic natural variety  74158 region  sidama farm  karamo washing station a little subjective personal description on this beans as one of our team usually do not enjoy anaerobic natural beans and on her first sip it is just an entirely different texture and experience for her this beans has our hearts on its first roast with such delicate texture and orange spectrum that reminds you of tangerine with layers of stonefruit that reminds you of nectarine and closed with that taste of oolong tea this is juicy yet tealike perfect for any time of the day

name: colombia eliecer ordez  instinct roastery  150 gram
description: process  washed variety  pink bourbon region  huila farm  el placer owned by pastor ordez finca el placer has been known for growing caturra and pink bourbon varieties as its highlight located in the region of huila colombia this farm is known for its microlots rather than bulk commercial lots el placer is a part of associacion los naranjos a community of small producers that has strict and careful procedures in processing its coffee resulting in consistency of high quality coffee this colombia has been nothing but a joy ever since we cup it in our cupping table and we are delighted to present it for you to try this coffee has balanced quality with red currant in the spotlight on your first sip layers of pomelo bright acidity and wrapped with sugarcane mellow sweetness

name: burundi kayanza natural  instinct roastery  150 gram
description: process  natural variety  bourbon farm  long miles region  kayanza a connection built from last year to osito brought us to this new region from ethiopia to our shelf we love when connections bring us a lot of excitements and new things to explore together a first time for us to exhibit burundi region coffee beans and it doesnt disappoint the littlest bit this burundi is sourced from long miles coffee farm a renowned coffee farm that develops washing station mainly on burundi with transparancy and hard work long miles has been known for its quality in specialty coffee industry this is for you who wants that juiciness of purple fruits with hint of chocolate liquor adding to its sweetness

name: caramel floral  instinct roastery espresso blend  200 gram
description: toraja pangopango washed  ethiopia washed the moment we cupped the samples from the toraja a few months ago we knew how the quality of the flavor that this toraja gives is just beautiful we knew how a lot of you also longs for another espresso blend from us so here we are presenting you with such collaboration this toraja gives you beautiful caramelish sweetness that has very round quality and also smooth at the same time then comes the acidity citrusy acidity coming from the ethiopian washed which creates such harmonious flavor making this a balanced espresso blend with sweetness but also that elegant aromatic quality

name: toraja pangopango washed  instinct roastery  200 gram
description: variety  slini bourbon process  washed region  tana toraja farm  aluk coffee altitude  1600 masl this local beans captured our heart on the cupping table when we sample this we feel a little excitement of adding another region of indonesia to our shelf this classic washed toraja from pangopango gives its charm with its clean finish cheery bright citrusy acidity that reminds you of lemon topped with acidity of stonefruit that gives balance to the lemon ish acidity and sweetness that wraps it off like honey

name: ethiopia sidama karama washed  instinct roastery  200 gram
description: region  bura karamo altitude  2200 masl process  washed variety  heirloom a big big smile in our roastery team upon cupping this ethiopian classic washed process we always know that a lot of you excited when we release any ethiopian beans we also always aim for giving you varieties of ethiopian beans this beautiful classic washed boasts about its refined acidity of mandarin orange with layers of bergamot and what makes this beans even more excellent is the fact that it has sweetness that reminds you of sugarcane purchase this if you want to find yourself sipping light refined cup of acidity with touch of balanced sweetness

name: bali berry  instinct roastery  200 gram
description: seasonal espresso blend for you a creation from one of our roastery team an idea to highlight our components for wholesale beans which hasnt come to spotlight to many this blend is based on our bali karana a cm natural beans that has been on our lineup for years partnered up with bali we go with the favorite blueberry apple the aceh blend and topping it off with brazil this blend is for you who loves a balanced coffee with notes of chocolate and fruitiness

name: p blend  instinct roastery  biji kopi  200 gram
description: please note before buying untuk permintaan digiling menjadi bubuk kopi mohon cantumkan di bagian notes karena jika tidak kami akan mengirimkan dalam bentuk biji kopi utuh terima kasih p for premium blend  darker roast instinct version  a blend made for people who love bigbodied coffee with low acidity yet still has the strong character and flavor of specialty coffee using 100 arabica specialty grade coffee suitable for milk or classic espresso taste  kopi susu

name: guatemala espresso  instinct coffee  biji kopi  200 gram
description: please note before buying untuk permintaan digiling menjadi bubuk kopi mohon cantumkan di bagian notes karena jika tidak kami akan mengirimkan dalam bentuk biji kopi utuh terima kasih varian lain utk kopi espresso dengan karakter low acidity creamy dan sweet kali ini datang dari guatemala guatemala merupakan favorite daerah kami selain brazil dimana brazil menghasilkan mouthfeel yang lebih berat full dengan notes chocolate nutty sedangkan guatemala menghasilkan rasa yang lebih bersih more rounded sweetness dikomplimen dengan rasa nutty dan juga sweetness seperti toffee varian espresso lain utk kamu yg suka karakter low acidity kopi pertama kali tiba di guatemala pada abad ke18 di antigua perkebunan mulai tersebar selama 150 tahun berikutnya sebagian besar dimiliki oleh penjajah eropa negara ini memperoleh kemerdekaan pada tahun 1821 dan produksi kopi melonjak menjadikan guatemala sebagai produsen kopi yang penting kopi ini berasal dekat kota jilotepeque di wilayah chimaltenango terdapat pertanian luas finca el retiro del quisaya peternakan ini didirikan 100 tahun yang lalu oleh keluarga ortega dan barubaru ini dijual ke organisasi arabigos del sur nama peternakan ini berasal dari sungai yang mengalir di dalam tanah tersebut perkebunan  el retiro quisaya varietas  bourbon proses dicuci sepenuhnya ketinggian  1800 meter di atas permukaan laut kota  kota  san martin jilotepeque wilayah  chimaltenango pemilik  arabigos del sur sa

name: bali karana cm natural  instinct coffee  biji kopi  200 gram
description: please note before buying untuk permintaan digiling menjadi bubuk kopi mohon cantumkan di bagian notes karena jika tidak kami akan mengirimkan dalam bentuk biji kopi utuh terima kasih origin  bali  kintamani producer  karana process  cm natural varietas  s795  kartika altitude  1200  1500 masl this is our third year working with bli edi from karana global they produce one of the best natural coffees in indonesia and we hope this years harvest also meets your expectations karana is a collaboration between two coffee professionals who share a common passion for exceptional coffee rodney glick australian and i kadek edi indonesian are both certified licensed q graders processors roasters and experts in the coffee supply chain karana farm process and trade indonesian specialty and commercial coffee based in ubud bali with a coffee bureau in medan sumatra embedded in balinese traditional village life with a focus on the global coffee market karana are focused on quality from farm to cup in 2021 at the first indonesian held cup of excellence karana achieved the highest scoring bali coffee as well as being ranked in the top 20 coffees overall

name: espresso caramel nutty  biji kopi espresso  500gr
description: please note before buying untuk permintaan digiling menjadi bubuk kopi mohon cantumkan di bagian notes karena jika tidak kami akan mengirimkan dalam bentuk biji kopi utuh terima kasih all time favorite espresso this is for you who looks for a low acidity with high body and sweetness in your cup suitable for your daily needs of espressobased drinks

name: biji kopi arabica colombia papayo inmaculada natural specialty arabica coffee beans  15gr biji
description: origin valle del cauca colombia variety papayoateng altitude 18002000 masl processing anaerobic natural farmer inmaculada fellow farms tasting notes plum orange  pineapple the papayo variety is rare outside of huila and little is known about how it arrived in colombia it was originally thought to be a caturra mutation but genetic testing by world coffee research indicates a close relationship with ethiopian landraces papayo cherries are distinctive with an elongated shape it is assumed that the local name comes from the papaya fruit  well also give you the brewing recommendation to brew the coffee with hario v60  limited stock  penting hanya bisa dalam bentuk biji agar menjaga beans sampai dalam keadaan aman dan intensitas rasanya tidak cepat menurun semua pesanan yang masuk lewat dari jam 3 sore akan dikirim keesokan harinya

name: kopi arabika bogor lactic washed 100 gr single origin specialty coffee  biji
description: halal id32110016691860324 origin bogor west java variety s795 sigarar utang and ateng super gayo35 ateng altitude 11001300 masl processing lactic washed farmer java kirana tasting notes orange almond  brown sugar these coffees are mixed varieties of s795 sigarar utang and ateng super gayo3 which are grown between 11001300 masl fresh cherries are picked and sorted coffee is pulped then undergoes 48 hours of fermentation in the controlled saline condition afterward the pulped cherry is washed until the mucilage is deattached from the parchment after being washed with fresh water the clean coffee parchment is dried for 12 days inside a moistureregulated uv greenhouse after its dried the coffee undergoes a resting process inside the parchment for 1 month before being hulled and ready to sell biji kopi dapat langsung di giling langsung sesuai permintaan  giling espresso  giling kasar  giling medium  giling halus  giling v60 disesuaikan dengan resep yang anda dapat penting semua pesanan yang masuk lewat dari jam 3 sore akan dikirim keesokan harinya kami akan berikan 8gr free sample beans sebagai bentuk penyesuaian karena harga bahan baku semakin meningkat free sample untuk cupping akan kami berikan sebanyak 8gr silahkan pilih 1 beans dari produk yang ada di etalase toko kami dan tulis di catatan saat check out pesanan beans di etalase special release tidak bisa dipilih untuk sample greatcoffeeforgreatpeople penting foto produk desain produk dapat berubah tanpa ada pemberitahuan karena sesuai stok kemasan kopi yang ada terimakasih

name: tapanuli sibadak washed dark room dried  filter  60g probat p01
description: tapanuli sibadak washed dark room dried notes yellow stone fruits white flowers tamarind lemon producer alex hutabarat  sibadak coffee region sitampurung tapanuli varietal ateng p88 sigararutang process washed dark room dried elevation 12501300 masl harvest september 2025 relationship 1 year price padi idr 350000kg a brief history about the farm located at 12501300 masl in sitampurung village north tapanuli sibadak coffee was established in 2017 by alex hutabarat alex applies organicleaning farming methods enriching soil with compost and minimizing pesticide use originally focused on p88 and ateng super he introduced sidra seeds in 2021 sourced from ecuador after seeing the varietys remarkable potential alex expanded sidra plantings and is now preparing to plant 30000 new seedlings at higher elevations this washed drd coffee begins with careful pulping and 24hour wet fermentation followed by a twostage drying approach five days of shadedrying then 25 days in alexs newly built dark room drying facility where temperature and humidity are controlled the result is a polished and refined cup that reveals new dimensions in tapanulis local hybrid varieties

name: ecuador la papaya geisha washed  filter  60g probat p01

name: jack runners roastery  sweet summer  roasted beans  grind fine 200 gram
description: biji kopi roast beans papandayan honey 200 gram  sweet summer   arabica papandayan honey process this coffee brings back memories of summer afternoons it also has a special caramel and mandarin flavor that is almost herbal but with overtones of sweet caramel for the process itself the coffee beans are picked at the best ripeness level later the outer layer of the cherry will be peeled so that what remains is only the mucilage layer and the coffee beans next the coffee will be dried in the sun like a natural process while most of the process on mount papandayan west java with an altitude of more than 1300 meters above sea level is completely washed and natural adding fermented cherries produces a consistent and flavorful fermentation creating a sweet and fruity coffee not to be missed all cherries are selectively picked then sorted to remove ripe and damaged cherries the cherries are then pureed within 6 hours of delivery once ground the coffee and remaining slime are placed on a raised bed to dry the longer fermentation time in processed coffee also allows the flavors to develop more when drying the parchment is sorted and sifted repeatedly to ensure even drying parchment takes an average of 10 to 14 days to dry everyday coffee drink asal  papandayan jawa barat ketinggian  13001600 mdpl varietas  typica linis proses dry fermentation 15 days notes sweet caramel mandarin palm sugar balance round mouthfeel profil panggang terbaik untuk filter profile roast medium  fine  giling halus tubruk  medium  giling medium v60 coffee maker manual brew vietnam drip  coarse  giling kasar cold drip cold brew manual brew teknik kasar aeropress

description: ethiopia guji harsu  natural  hana roastery  filter coffee  kopi grown in ethiopias renowned yirgacheffe region this coffee is produced by smallholder farmers in the town of gedeban area celebrated for its exceptional washed coffees and recognized as a distinct microregion the landscape is defined by rolling hills lush vegetation and rich fertile soil where coffee flourishes at elevations above 2000 meters cherries are selectively handpicked and delivered to nearby collection points usually within 5 km of each producers home during delivery farmers carefully remove any overripe underripe or damaged cherries before the lot is combined and transported to the wet mill once a day these consolidated cherries arrive at the mill where they undergo sorting floating and depulping they are then fermented in concrete tanks for 6672 hours fully washed graded through channels and moved to raised beds for drying over several weeks the coffee is turned frequently until it reaches a stable moisture content of 12 ensuring clean consistent quality this washed coffee showcases a beautiful citrus notes and sweetness which reminds us of earl grey tea and tangerine followed by honeylike sweetness region yirgacheffe ethiopia process full washed elevation 2000 masl varietals jarc 74110 producer mercanta what we found earl grey tangerine honey net weight 100200500 gram roasted for filter mohon tulis di notes jika ingin digrind atau digiling kami menyediakan 2 pilihan gilingan medium grind  pour over coarse grind  pour over french press aeropress  1 pengiriman paling lambat akan kami lakukan 1 hari setelah pemesanan pesanan yang masuk setelah jam 1400 kemungkinan besar akan dikirim hari esoknya 2 kami tidak melakukan pengiriman pada hari minggu dan tanggal merah 3 waktu ideal untuk menyeduh adalah 10 sampai 1 bulan setelah tanggal roast date 5 bantuan teman teman untuk memberikan ulasan bintang 5 akan sangat membantu kami 6 happy brewing
